div.p:
BUT not to purſue this too far—I proceed to obſerve upon Sect. II.—Your Author having ſtated the Queſtion, Has Jeſus Chriſt any God over him, who has greater Authority and greater Ability than himſelf or not?
propoſes hence to demonſtrate the Affirmative, by ſhewing, Firſt, that Jeſus Chriſt expreſly ſpeaks of another God than himſelf.—Secondly, That he acknowledges this God to be above or over himſelf;
               —And laſtly, That he wants thoſe ſupereminent and infinite Perfections which belong only to the Lord God of Gods.—
